                    "company": "University of Amsterdam",
                    "description": "This was a post-doctoral research within a research project funded by an European Research Council (ERC) Starting Grant titled \"Public-Private Security Assemblages\". This project investigates to what extent security assemblages function as hybrid governance structures, and the implications this has for how different groups enact and experience citizenship. It will examine how urban spaces and populations are governed, and how political subjectivities shift, as a result of these hybrid forms of security provision. Within this project, I conducted a comparative analysis of these security assemblages in Kingston, Nairobi, and Jerusalem.\nSee: www.security-assemblages.com",
