                    "company": "Utrecht University",
                    "description": "Department of Cultural Anthropology, Faculty of Social and Behavioural Sciences, Utrecht University. This PhD research focuses on private security companies and their niche within policing the streets of Durban, South Africa. Through a framework of local security networks, this research analyzes their daily interactions with other policing agents. This research is based on 18 months of ethnographic fieldwork conducted in Durban, South Africa. This research was funded by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Netherlands through the IS-academy programme. \n\nBesides the research project, this position has included other tasks, such as:\n- Chairperson of the PhD working group at the Department of Cultural Anthropology (2009-2011)\n- Representative of the Department of Cultural Anthropology in the PhD council of the Graduate School , Utrecht University (2011)\n- Organising colloquims and master classes at the Department of Cultural Anthropology\n- Providing guest lectures",
